wiki.content:
"Suck My Kiss" is the third single from the Red Hot Chili Peppers' fifth studio album Blood Sugar Sex Magik released in 1991. "Suck My Kiss" was released as a single in 1992 in Australia only; a music video was made using footage from the "Funky Monks" documentary directed by Gavin Bowden. The song was included on the band's Greatest Hits compilation.
 
 The song was covered by Richard Cheese and Lounge Against the Machine on his 2000 album Lounge Against the Machine.
 
 The song is featured as an unlockable track in Guitar Hero III.
 
 The song was also used in an episode of Beavis and Butt-Head.
